title: MediaJel Public API
description: GraphQL API for managing advertising campaigns, organizations, and campaign orders on the MediaJel platform.

categories.name: Authentication
categories.description: Authenticate and obtain JWT tokens for API access.

categories.name: Paid Search
categories.description: Query paid search campaigns, reports, and performance data.

categories.name: SEO
categories.description: Query SEO summaries, units, and configurations.

categories.name: Campaign Orders
categories.description: Query campaign orders including budgets, schedules, and performance data.

categories.name: Campaigns
categories.description: Query advertising campaigns, checklists, and reviews.

categories.name: Line Items
categories.description: Query line items with detailed performance metrics and targeting configuration.

categories.name: Audiences
categories.description: Query audience segments, hashed email lists, and demographics.

categories.name: Creatives
categories.description: Query creative assets, ad groups, media, and ad units.

categories.name: Targeting
categories.description: Query geographic and events-based targeting configurations.

categories.name: Organizations
categories.description: Query and manage advertising organizations and advertisers.

categories.name: Licenses
categories.description: Query license information and compliance data.

categories.name: Users & Roles
categories.description: Query users, roles, and permissions.

categories.name: Products
categories.description: Query products, brands, catalog items, strains, and recommendations.

categories.name: Locations
categories.description: Query location data and geographic information.

categories.name: Messaging
categories.description: Query messages, notifications, and conversations.

categories.name: Content
categories.description: Query articles, editorials, and release reports.

categories.name: Loyalty

categories.name: Billing
categories.description: Query billing, invoices, agreements, and fee configurations.

categories.name: Projects
categories.description: Query tasks, projects, and milestones.

categories.name: Analytics

categories.name: Integrations

authSignIn.description: Authenticate with your Cognito credentials to obtain JWT tokens. The returned `accessToken` is used in the `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header, and your organization ID is sent in the `Key` header for all subsequent requests.
